      "content": "# GET /user Endpoint Documentation\n## Overview\nThe GET /user endpoint retrieves the profile information for the currently logged-in user.\n## Authentication\nThis endpoint requires a valid authentication token in the Authorization header.\n## Request Parameters\nNo query parameters are required for this request.\n## Response Format\nThe response is returned as a JSON object containing user details.\n## Response Fields\nThe `id` field contains the unique user identifier.\n## Response Fields\nThe `username` field contains the display name of the user.\n## Response Fields\nThe `email` field contains the user's registered email address.\n## Response Fields\nThe `created_at` field contains the timestamp of account creation.\n## Response Fields\nThe `is_active` field indicates if the account is currently active.\n## Error Handling\nInvalid requests will return a 401 Unauthorized status code.\n## Error Handling\nInvalid requests will return a 403 Forbidden status code.\n## Error Handling\nInvalid requests will return a 500 Internal Server Error status code.\n## Examples\nSee the API examples section for request/response samples.\n## Examples\nSee the API examples section for request/response samples.\n## Security",
      "source": "target",
